    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Use this method to create a trusted app instance, which both identifies an app and provides data that can be used to ensure that the app hasn’t been altered since the instance was created."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "You can use the created instance as input to the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/security/1393522-secaccesscreate"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " method, which creates an access instance. The access instance, in turn, is used as input to the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/security/1395210-seckeychainitemsetaccess"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " function to specify the set of apps that are trusted to access a specific keychain item. "
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
